Building Strategic Risk Plans
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Design a strategic risk management framework that aligns cybersecurity risks with human behavior and organizational culture
Implement role-based risk assessments using Python
Create prioritization matrices for risk management decisions
Develop automated tools for risk analysis and visualization
Build data-driven risk management plans for organizational contexts
Prerequisites
Basic Python programming (functions, dictionaries, loops, file I/O)
Understanding of cybersecurity risk concepts
Familiarity with Linux command line
Basic knowledge of organizational roles and security responsibilities
